        <pb xml:id="F32050726" n="1" facs="https://cdm17313.contentdm.oclc.org/iiif/2/mdah:13924/full/full/0/default.jpg"/>
        <div xml:id="OTP32050726">
        <fw type="pageNum">Page 1</fw>
          <p corresp='TTP32050726P0' xml:id='OTP32050726P0'><rs ref='#S51788'>Vicksburg</rs> Miss March 25, 1862
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32050726P1' xml:id='OTP32050726P1'><rs ref='#S32008264'> M<hi rend='underline'>rs</hi> Gov<add place='above'><hi rend='underline'>r</hi></add> Poindexter</rs>
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32050726P2' xml:id='OTP32050726P2'>Madam
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32050726P3' xml:id='OTP32050726P3'>I have just received a letter from <rs ref='#S32008265'>Jacob Ozelle</rs> wishing me to write to you &amp; state what I know of his former habits—I would say that I have known him several years and have never known him otherwise than an upright honest man—and I firmly believe that whatever has led to his <rs ref='#S69535'>incarceration</rs> in the <rs ref='#S54861'>Penitentiary</rs> has been the work of some other person—&amp;as he was ever ready to trust others—and Consequently easy led into error—&amp; as you may judge from his being so easy drawn <del rend='overstrike'>in</del>to invest his all in a partnership with that worthless fellow—<rs ref='#S32008266'>Frank?</rs>—who had nothing to lose,—but <rs ref='#S63934'>judge</rs> &amp; <rs ref='#S32008267'>Mrs Montgomery</rs> know him well for he was in their service for some time—and there are few persons who know the Judge or his lady that are prepared to doubt their veracity
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32050726P4' xml:id='OTP32050726P4'>I am <lb/>
Your very obt servt
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32050726P5' xml:id='OTP32050726P5'><rs ref='#S32008268'>Charles Allen</rs> 
</p>


        </div>
